<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 07 at 3:20PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Toombs,
southeastern Wheeler and southern Montgomery Counties through 345 PM
EDT...
At 320 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Charlotteville, or 11
miles north of Hazlehurst, moving southeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Uvalda, Alston, South Thompson, English Eddy, Center, Toombs Central,
Rock Springs, Cedar Crossing, Jordan, Charlotteville, McNatt Falls
and Grays Landing.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
